    "Question": {
      "content": "The law of conservation of charges states that:",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "total quantity of charge in any process does not change",
        "energy and momentum of the charges is conserved",
        "charges are the smallest unit of matter",
        "charges are immobile"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "total quantity of charge in any process does not change"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<p>The law of conservation of charge states that the <b>net electric charge</b> in an isolated system remains constant. This is fundamental to electromagnetism and is expressed mathematically as:</p> \\[ \\sum q_{initial} = \\sum q_{final} \\]"
    },
